Name: persistent fetal circulation syndrome
Definition: A relapsing fever that is characterized by relapsing or recurring episodes of fever
Synonym: persistent pulmonary hypertension of the newborn

Name: pulmonary venoocclusive disease
Definition: A eccrine sweat gland neoplasm that is characterized by isolated well-circumscribed dermal nodule existent for a prolonged duration of time.

Name: obsolete pulmonary vascular disorder
Definition: A eccrine sweat gland neoplasm that is characterized by isolated well-circumscribed dermal nodule existent for a prolonged duration of time.

Name: obsolete spinal vascular disorder
